gomodel:SYNGO_24  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Antibodies against np65 and recombinant neuroplastin extracellular domains prevent maintenance of LTP at CA1 synapses in hippocampal slices (fig. 4, table 1). Homophilic interaction in trans is shown in heterologous cells (fig. 5)\n\n67/12/2016 Pim:\n- Figure 5 shows trans-interaction between recombinant np65/55 proteins in homophilic aggregation assay with microspheres. This would support a inference to pre-2-post-synapse adhesion when combined with evidence on localization to \"presynaptic membrane\" and \"postsynaptic membrane\".\n- regulation of synaptic transmission is shown with LTP experiments (Fig.4).\n\nA \"signaling\" role that underlies the effect of NP interference is **inferred** from the established role NP initiating intracellular signaling cascades in the synapse (PMID:25040546 - Review describing potential signaling pathways in transsynaptic signaling via NPs). Experimental description: Fig.4: \"LTP experiments were performed on transverse slices (400 μm) of the right hippocampus from 8-wk-old male **Wistar rats**, strain Shoe...\"\nFig.5: species is not relevant because these are heterologous cells." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_24" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

